This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it focuses on the use of recurrent neural networks for epidemic forecasting. It may also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with graph-structured data. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for sparsification of the network weights. The paper also deals with systems and control (cs.SY) as it involves forecasting and prediction. Finally, it may fall under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as it involves the use of neural networks.
